Akhirnya nonton #Gundala. Awang so cool!!!!

It's really difficult not to compare #Gundala to pre-existing superhero movies from Hollywood especially when it's trying so hard to be one. Or at least feel like one. You can tell most of the lines feel like they were originally written in English.

#Gundala has very little or no level of originality. Beginning from the title card up until the end credits I can tell you where they probably draw inspiration from. With the end credits being the one that's so obviously trying to mimic Captain America: Civil War's.

They did the title character dirty. They didn't have the intention whatsoever to tell his story properly. All they cared about is how to cram as much as stuff from the books. It ended up getting in the way of letting him be the main focus of the story. Such a disservice. #Gundala

Finally picked it up bcs my cousin wouldn't shut up about it. I was instantly skeptical when I saw the runtime. I said it couldn't possibly be justified. And it couldn't indeed. I was so sure that at least an hour had passed when actually it had been only 40mins. #Gundala

Semiotics in #Gundala comic book. Petugas sekuriti bernama (A)ziz digambarkan tak berdaya karena nyawanya diancam menggunakan pisau. How can you not connect it with the current political situation dimana kelompok 212 konsisten mengusung narasi dizolimi oleh pemerintah?

Smart move by Ardian Syah to conceal the nomor cantik 212 in #Gundala as Aziz so readers can't really file official complaint to @mnccomics @bumilangitcom. But still you can even make a connection with P.A. 212 abbr. Persaudaraan Alumni 212. Or Aziz = Alumni 212.

Gave Ardian Syah the benefit of the doubt so I bought #Gundala comic the one based on @jokoanwar screenplay. Just a couple of pages down and I already spotted 212. So @amasna was right when he said something in line with canceling #Gundala comic because Ardian drew it.

BCU is an ambitious project and #Gundala gives us promises of what Indonesian filmmakers can do. #Gundala has truly come out as a new hope for Indonesian cinema.

There's still so much I want to talk about #Gundala but all in all the good things in #Gundala surpass way over the bad ones. It's a hella kickin' way to kick-off a phase. The benchmark is already so high I'm gonna keep my expectations low for the next movie.

In this age when all heroes we see are SUPERheroes--they are god-like or too-good-to-be-true or otherworldly even--#Gundala actually rises among these overly-saturated crowd as the hero of the people from the people and for the people.

I especially love #Gundala because really I've never seen anything like it. It resonates strongly with Indonesian culture and yet it reminds us of the definition of a hero as the person who fights for the right cause and protects the weak the hopeless and the desperate.

I watched #Gundala and gave it an 8.2 out of 10. I wasn't sure about it and even more so after knowing others' mixed reactions towards it. So today I took the chance to revisit just to be certain of my own review. Nah I ain't changing my score.
